All Packages

  • Package Summary 
    Package Description
    DAO
    The DAO (Data Access Object) contains the data access logic for the application.
    Models
    The Models object primarily encapsulate data fields and provide methods for accessing and manipulating that data.
    Secrets
    Secrets provide the name, user, and password for necessary for Database access.
    Services
    Service packages provide logic to operate on the data sent to and from the DAO and the client.
    Styles
    Styles package provides the styling for the java swing pages
    ui.base
    This package contains the essential abstract classes and interfaces that will be consistently used throughout the application.
    ui.base.wrappers
    This includes the wrapper objects that will contain the reference of an object.
    ui.components
    UI Components include the reusable UI components that can be used across one or multiple pages.
    ui.controller
    UI Controllers contains a group of related page elements that usually hold shared states and handle events/services that occur.
    ui.events.eventbroadcasters
    Event Broadcasters provide the ability to store multiple objects who are subscribed to that event call and executes their unique action once a certain event occurs
    ui.events.eventbroadcasters.listenerinterface
    Listener Interfaces provide a backbone to the eventbroadcasters.
    ui.events.eventhandlers.buttonactions.ItemOrderCustomizationPage
    Eventhandlers/ButtonActions are event actions that are associated with a JButton/Button components.
    ui.events.eventhandlers.buttonactions.loginpage
    Eventhandlers/ButtonActions are event actions that are associated with a JButton/Button components.
    ui.events.eventhandlers.buttonactions.NavBar
    Eventhandlers/ButtonActions are event actions that are associated with a JButton/Button components.
    ui.events.eventhandlers.eventactions
    Event Actions are not associated to any java swing Application Component calling on it.
    ui.framework
    Framework.States: Contains essential states that need to be shared across multiple UI components (sharedstates that are in controllers) Framework : The ones that puts together all neccessary UI elements and their associated controllers to run the application
    ui.framework.states
    Framework.States: Contains essential states that need to be shared across multiple UI components (sharedstates that are in controllers)
    ui.pages.dockedpages
    DockedPages are the UI pages that include a navbar alongside these screens.
    ui.pages.fullpages
    FullPages are the UI pages that occupy the entire screen.
